      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so u think the principles are what matters mostly. but if the goal is to apply \"timeless principles,\" some people say originalism is actually pretty bad at that because it relies so much on what people thought 200 years ago, which is basically just a snapshot of one specific time and place. isn't that kind of a flawed way to run a modern legal system?",
